# MoodCode — Project Context

Read MOODCODE_CONTEXT.md in full before every response.

## Current phase: Phase 3 — Spotify + Weather + Git signals
- Phases 1 (MVP) and 2 (weighted engine + typing) are complete and deployed
- We are building: Spotify OAuth + polling, Weather signal, Git signal
- Do NOT implement custom moods or Marketplace publishing yet (Phase 4)

## Architecture rules
- No auth system — userId is a UUID from VS Code globalState. No JWT, no login.
- Dashboard is personal — no multi-user, no roles.
- shared/ types are source of truth — change types there first, then update consumers
- Always recompile shared before building extension or dashboard
- Extension uses esbuild bundling: `npm run bundle`, not `npm run compile`
- Extension must work offline — falls back to DEFAULT_BRACKETS + DEFAULT_SIGNAL_WEIGHTS

## Infrastructure
- Backend: Railway (not localhost)
- Dashboard: Vercel (not localhost)
- DB: MongoDB Atlas

## Key behaviours
- First-match-wins for bracket evaluation (top-to-bottom)
- Spotify + weather signals come FROM backend via WebSocket — extension never calls these APIs directly
- Git signal runs locally in extension via child_process — no backend involvement
- Weather cached 15 minutes server-side
- Spotify tokens refreshed server-side automatically
- Weighted mood engine already built — just update signalScores.spotify / .weather / .git
- SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI must be the Railway URL — cannot be localhost

## Source of truth
Full project context is in MOODCODE_CONTEXT.md at the monorepo root.